{"sha": "796b7cbac3d553a91d37c3961b9391fb7e19d0c6", "node_id": "C_kwDOANBUbNoAKDc5NmI3Y2JhYzNkNTUzYTkxZDM3YzM5NjFiOTM5MWZiN2UxOWQwYzY", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Iain Buclaw", "email": "ibuclaw@gdcproject.org", "date": "2022-04-26T13:10:09Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Iain Buclaw", "email": "ibuclaw@gdcproject.org", "date": "2022-04-26T13:32:11Z"}, "message": "libphobos: Don't call free on the TLS array in the emutls destroy function.\n\nFixes a segfault seen on Darwin when a GC scan is ran after a thread has\nbeen destroyed.  As the global emutlsArrays hash still has a reference\nto the array itself, and tries to iterate all elements.\n\nSetting the length to zero frees all allocated elements in the array,\nand ensures that it is skipped when the _d_emutls_scan is called.\n\nlibphobos/ChangeLog:\n\n\t* libdruntime/gcc/emutls.d (emutlsDestroyThread): Clear the per-thread\n\tTLS array, don't call free().", "tree": {"sha": "9efbe189e65e04d19b77e06ab1605eeecbb6c6e3", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/trees/9efbe189e65e04d19b77e06ab1605eeecbb6c6e3"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/commits/796b7cbac3d553a91d37c3961b9391fb7e19d0c6", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/796b7cbac3d553a91d37c3961b9391fb7e19d0c6", "html_url": "https://github.com/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commit/796b7cbac3d553a91d37c3961b9391fb7e19d0c6", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/796b7cbac3d553a91d37c3961b9391fb7e19d0c6/comments", "author": {"login": "ibuclaw", "id": 397929, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM5NzkyOQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/397929?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ibuclaw", "html_url": "https://github.com/ibuclaw", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ibuclaw/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/user